{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9a3979c7-67e6-47a8-bfee-ceca80cf7884","content":"Here's what you need:\n\n### Environment Variables\n\nSet these on your container for .NET 11 NativeAOT automatic crash dumps:\n\n| Variable | Value | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` | `1` | Enables automatic dump on crash |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` | `4` | Full dump (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full) |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` | `/tmp/dumps/core.%p.%t` | Dump path with PID + timestamp tokens |\n| `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` | `/opt/tools/createdump` | Points to your custom createdump location |\n\n### Pod Spec Changes\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: your-app\n      env:\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/tmp/dumps/core.%p.%t\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 4Gi\n```\n\n### Key notes\n\n- **`%p` and `%t`** expand to PID and unix timestamp, preventing overwrites on repeated crashes.\n- **`sizeLimit: 4Gi`** on the `emptyDir` prevents a full dump from filling the node's disk — adjust based on your app's memory footprint.\n- **NativeAOT** doesn't bundle `createdump`, so `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` is required to point to your pre-installed copy.\n- Use `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=1` (Mini) if you only need stack traces and want smaller files.\n\nTo **retrieve dumps**, either add a sidecar that uploads from `/tmp/dumps` to blob storage, or use `kubectl cp <pod>:/tmp/dumps ./local-dumps` before the pod is evicted.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d24329aa-0fc9-4014-9e1e-3a8a231bc847","outputTokens":579,"requestId":"C3D6:1EBA3E:1BE2BF5:1F7288C:6A07C21E"},"id":"a74214ce-3d2e-48a2-942c-63e1b2b712e9","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:02:32.875Z","parentId":"72583c26-2c90-4e80-8d7a-b200e5692da1"}
